;DNA MOTOR PROTEIN, WHICH IS BOTH REQUIRED TO MOVE DNA
 OUT OF THE REGION OF THE SEPTUM DURING CELL DIVISION AND FOR THE
 SEPTUM FORMATION. TRACKS DNA IN AN ATP-DEPENDENT MANNER BY
 GENERATING POSITIVE SUPERCOILS IN FRONT OF IT AND NEGATIVE
 SUPERCOILS BEHIND IT (BY SIMILARITY).
